{"qid": "q060", "question": "In pgvector, when should I pick HNSW over IVFFlat for my index?", "expected_answer": "Choose HNSW when you want better speed-recall query performance and can accept slower builds and more memory; it also needs no training step so it can be built on an empty table. IVFFlat builds faster and uses less memory but has lower query performance.", "qtype": "factoid", "gold": [{"doc_id": "pgvector/README", "locator": "better query performance than IVFFlat", "grade": "primary"}, {"doc_id": "pgvector/README", "locator": "faster build times and uses less memory than HNSW", "grade": "supporting"}]}
