{"qid": "q062", "question": "How can I build an index on a big PostgreSQL table without locking out writes for the whole build?", "expected_answer": "Use CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY, which builds the index without taking a lock that blocks writes (at the cost of a slower build).", "qtype": "vocab-mismatch", "gold": [{"doc_id": "postgres/sql-createindex", "locator": "CONCURRENTLY", "grade": "primary"}]}
