{"qid": "q064", "question": "I'm using a third-party client in FastAPI that tells me to call it with await. How do I keep that from blocking the server while it waits?", "expected_answer": "Declare the path operation with async def and await the library call; FastAPI runs it on the event loop so other requests proceed concurrently while it waits.", "qtype": "vocab-mismatch", "gold": [{"doc_id": "fastapi/async", "locator": "call them with `await`", "grade": "primary"}], "notes": "Failure-2 target: 'blocking'/'slow call' vs 'concurrency/async/await'."}
